<headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 16 at 5:57PM EST  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...AN AREA OF HEAVY SNOW WILL AFFECT PARTS OF LAPEER...MACOMB...AND
ST. CLAIR COUNTIES...
HAZARDS...An area of heavy snow which can rapidly reduce visibility
to less than a quarter of a mile and produce snow rate around 1 inch
per hour.
LOCATION AND MOVEMENT...At 555 PM EST, an area of heavy snow was
along and north of a line extending from near Lakeport to near
Emmett to Dryden and moving southeast at 15 MPH.
THIS AREA OF HEAVY SNOW WILL BE NEAR...
Port Huron around 615 PM EST.
Marysville and Armada around 645 PM EST.
St. Clair around 655 PM EST.
Memphis around 705 PM EST.
Richmond around 710 PM EST.
Marine City around 815 PM EST.
This includes the following highways...
I-94 between mile markers 247 and 273.
I-69 between mile markers 149 and 199.
SAFETY INFO...
Use extra caution if you must travel into or through this area of
heavy snow. Rapid changes in visibility and potentially slick roads
may lead to accidents.
&amp;&amp;</description>
